<TITLE> German rail union says to strike later in week </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BERLIN, Oct 22 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The German train drivers' union said on Monday it will strike on Thursday and Friday, escalating its wage dispute with national rail operator Deutsche Bahn. The strikes will affect regional trains and urban commuter services from 2 a.m. (0000 GMT) on Thursday until 8 a.m. (0600) on Friday, the union said. Long-distance intercity trains and freight trains will not be affected. A series of one-day strikes has caused millions of commuters delays across the country this month. "Deutsche Bahn has not offered the German train drivers' union (GDL) a better wage deal, therefore, GDL has called on its members ... to strike," the union said in a statement on Monday. The GDL, which represents 34,000 train drivers, is seeking pay rises of up to 31 percent and an independent collective labour agreeme
